Write a C program to compute the monthly pay of 100 employees using each employeeâ€—s name, basic pay. The DA is computed as 52% of the basic pay. Gross-salary (basic pay + DA). Print the employees name and gross salary.

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    char name[100][50];      // To store 100 employee names
    float basic[100];        // To store basic pay
    float da, gross;
    int i;

    printf("Enter the name and basic pay of 100 employees:\n");

    for (i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
        printf("\nEmployee %d\n", i + 1);

        printf("Name: ");
        scanf("%s", name[i]);     // Reads name (single word)

        printf("Basic Pay: ");
        scanf("%f", &basic[i]);
    }

    printf("\n---------------------------------------------\n");
    printf("Employee Name\t\tGross Salary\n");
    printf("---------------------------------------------\n");

    for (i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
        da = 0.52 * basic[i];          // 52% DA
        gross = basic[i] + da;

        printf("%-20s\t%.2f\n", name[i], gross);
    }

    return 0;
}
